T1	Intervention 247 612	Sixteen patients who had chronic mitral regurgitation due to myxomatous degeneration were randomized to preservation (Pres group, n = 8) or no preservation (No Pres group, n = 8) of the chordae tendineae and papillary muscles during mitral valve replacement. Rest and exercise nuclear ventriculograms were performed early (3 months) and late (5 years) after surgery
